content:
Chat deployment settings control the functionality available to agents and their supervisors while chatting with customers.

Available in: Performance Editions, Developer Edition orgs created after June 14, 2012, Essentials, Unlimited, and Enterprise Editions with Service Cloud or Sales Cloud.

The legacy chat product is scheduled for retirement on February 14, 2026. Migrate to Messaging for In-App and Web before that date.

Apply settings when creating or editing a Chat deployment:

* Basic Information:
	+ Chat Deployment Name: names the deployment.
	+ Developer Name: sets the API name for this deployment.
	+ Chat Window Title: sets the chat window title as it appears to customers.
	+ Allow Visitors to Save Transcripts: indicates whether customers can save transcripts.
	+ Allow Access to Pre-Chat API: indicates whether developers can access pre-chat information.
* Permitted Domains: determines the domains that can host the deployment.
* Enable Custom Timeouts:
	+ Idle Connection Warning Duration: indicates the duration before a warning is sent.
	+ Idle Connection Timeout Duration: indicates the duration before the chat ends.
* Chat Window Branding:
	+ Branding Image Site: associates the deployment with a Salesforce Site.
	+ Chat Window Branding Image: sets the custom graphic in the customer's chat window.
	+ Mobile Chat Window Branding Image: sets the custom graphic for mobile access.
title: Chat Deployment Settings in Service Cloud
